The paper deals with the construction of codes for asymmetric channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the Varshamov–Tenengol’ts–Constantin–Rao codes, which are a class of error-correcting codes (cs.CR). The methods used in the paper involve generalized code concatenation, which is a technique commonly used in coding theory and can be classified under data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the superiority of the constructed codes compared to existing codes, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI).
